subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Cave surrounded by Caatinga environment (
Figure 1
), semi-arid climate with a dry season spanning 6–8 months, from mid-autumn to mid-spring (
Conti and Furlan 2003
; 
Fernandes et al. 2019
). Live specimens were observed attached to hard surfaces such as rocks and logs (
Figure 2
(i)), always in the water. All specimens were observed in the aphotic zone of the cavern.
